The Economics 101 story is that markets respond to shortages through price =
signals. If a widget factory burns down, there will be a shortage of widget=
s, widget users will pay higher prices to secure their scarce widgets, and =
entrepreneurs, seeing those high prices, will jump in to build their own wi=
dget factories and solve the shortfall.=C2=A0
Of course in the real world this mechanism is imperfect and not instantaneo=
us: If there=E2=80=99s a shortage of widgets and the price spikes, you can=
=E2=80=99t necessarily open a widget factory tomorrow. You need expertise a=
nd capital and raw materials and workers to respond to the price signal.
The =E2=80=A6=C2=A0let=E2=80=99s say Topics in Money Stuff Economics Semina=
r version of this story would mention that markets also sometimes respond t=
o shortages through=C2=A0con artists.
  [1]
=C2=A0When a widget factory burns down and people need widgets, there are n=
ot necessarily a lot of unemployed widget manufacturers hanging around read=
y to spring into action to solve the shortage. But there=C2=A0are, absolute=
ly, a lot of con artists hanging around pretending to sell gold bars or can=
nabis or crypto or whatever the Last Thing was, and=C2=A0their=C2=A0costs o=
f pivoting to the Current Thing are very low. They do not need to retool a =
factory or source raw materials. Just take the email that is like =E2=80=9C=
send me $1 million and I will get you a guaranteed 20% return in a month by=
 yield farming in DeFi=E2=80=9D and search-and-replace =E2=80=9Cyield farmi=
ng in DeFi=E2=80=9D with =E2=80=9Cmanufacturing scarce widgets.=E2=80=9D
Or =E2=80=9Csupplying scarce baby formula.=E2=80=9D Or =E2=80=9Cproviding m=
edical aid to Ukraine.=E2=80=9D Or =E2=80=9Cimporting N95 masks to fight Co=
vid.=E2=80=9D If you read the news and see that there=E2=80=99s a high-prof=
ile shortage of some good, you can just pretend to supply it! And gullible =
investors, who also read the news, will be excited to give you money.
This is not any sort of advice, I do not recommend it, I would not do it my=
self, but oh boy did Eliyahu Weinstein (allegedly) do it.=C2=A0In 2013, Wei=
nstein pleaded guilty to running a $200 million real estate Ponzi scheme. I=
n 2012 and 2013, while he was out on bail for that Ponzi scheme, he did ano=
ther financial scam  involving =E2=80=9Cpurported sales of pre-IPO Facebook=
 shares and Florida real estate=E2=80=9D; he pleaded guilty to that one in =
2014. He was sentenced to a total of 24 years in prison for all of this, bu=
t in January 2021 President Donald Trump commuted his sentence and let him =
out of prison. I don=E2=80=99t know why Trump let him out, but possibly he =
admired Weinstein=E2=80=99s moxie and sense of humor and wanted to see what=
 else he=E2=80=99d get up to.
That faith in him was richly rewarded yesterday, when Weinstein was charged=
 by the  US Securities and Exchange Commission and  federal prosecutors in =
New Jersey with doing a new Ponzi scheme in the two years since he left pri=
son. Pre-IPO Facebook shares were very much the current thing in 2012, befo=
re Facebook went public, but in 2021 through 2023  the things were apparent=
ly:
=09=E2=80=9CIn or around late 2021, Optimus [one of Weinstein=E2=80=99s com=
panies]=C2=A0started raising money directly from a small number of investor=
s to finance purported transactions related to COVID-19 medical supplies.=
=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9CIn or around May 2022, WEINSTEIN (posing as Mike Konig=
) asked CC-1 and CC-2 [two unnamed alleged co-conspirators] to raise money =
from investors to finance the purchase and delivery=C2=A0of three million f=
irst-aid kits (=E2=80=98FAKs=E2=80=99) to USAID to be distributed to the pe=
ople of Ukraine during the Russia-Ukraine war (the =E2=80=98FAK deal=E2=80=
=99).=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9CIn or around May 2022, WEINSTEIN (posing as Mike =
Konig), asked CC-1 and CC-2 to raise additional money to finance Company-1=
=E2=80=99s purchase of 100 million N95 masks (the =E2=80=98N95 Mask deal=E2=
=80=99).=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9CSimilarly, in or around early August 2022, WEI=
NSTEIN (posing as Mike Konig) asked CC-1 and CC-2 to raise money to finance=
 the purchase of approximately 29 shipping containers of baby formula from =
[alleged co-conspirator Alaa Mohamed] HATTAB=E2=80=99s company, Hattab Glob=
al, in order to capitalize on supply chain issues which had created a=C2=A0=
shortage in baby formula (the =E2=80=98Formula deal=E2=80=99).=E2=80=9D

Just pick a thing in the news, and he was allegedly pretending to supply it=
. Of course prosecutors say he was not actually doing any of these things a=
nd was instead stealing the money, then raising more (from the next thing) =
to Ponzi it up and pay fake returns to the earlier investors. If you raise =
money from investors to pretend to source Covid-19 supplies, and you tell t=
hem it was a huge success, then you can raise more money from investors to =
pretend to supply medical aid to Ukraine and use that money to pay your fak=
e returns to the Covid people. Here=E2=80=99s a sample pitch email:
We successfully completed our first formula deal with 4 x 28,200 800g Cans =
(4 Containers). That=E2=80=99s 112,200 cans of formula being distributed to=
 families in Texas at fair prices. Needless to say, we felt so good about t=
his one, that we have another deal in the pipeline for 29 more containers. =
And it is LIVE. If you want in on this deal, Offering is 25% within 3-4 Mon=
ths (Although we think it will be faster). Funding on this is open from 8/0=
8-8/19. ACt [sic] now,=E2=80=A6 Only 4mm in funding room left!
It seems that Weinstein called himself =E2=80=9CMike Konig=E2=80=9D for the=
 obvious reason that he had an extensive criminal record for frauds and did=
n=E2=80=99t want potential investors to know about it. (=E2=80=9CNo one wou=
ld ever give=C2=A0you a penny if they knew who I was . . . because I have a=
 bad reputation,=E2=80=9D Weinstein allegedly said at a meeting recorded by=
 law enforcement, oops.) And=C2=A0some of his alleged co-conspirators knew =
him as Mike Konig until this alleged hilarious dramatic reveal:

