10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Good Ponzi</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Economics 101 story is that markets respon=
d to shortages through price signals. If a widget factory burns down, there=
 will be a shortage of widgets, widget users will pay higher prices to secu=
re their scarce widgets, and entrepreneurs, seeing those high prices, will =
jump in to build their own widget factories and solve the shortfall.=C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course in the real world this mechanism is =
imperfect and not instantaneous: If there=E2=80=99s a shortage of widgets a=
nd the price spikes, you can=E2=80=99t necessarily open a widget factory to=
morrow. You need expertise and capital and raw materials and workers to res=
pond to the price signal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The =E2=80=A6=C2=A0let=E2=80=99s say Topics in=
 Money Stuff Economics Seminar version of this story would mention that mar=
kets also sometimes respond to shortages through=C2=A0<em>con artists</em>.=
<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: trans=
parent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0When a widget factory burns down and people need widgets, there a=
re not necessarily a lot of unemployed widget manufacturers hanging around =
ready to spring into action to solve the shortage. But there=C2=A0<em>are</=
em>, absolutely, a lot of con artists hanging around pretending to sell gol=
d bars or cannabis or crypto or whatever the Last Thing was, and=C2=A0<em>t=
heir=C2=A0</em>costs of pivoting to the Current Thing are very low. They do=
 not need to retool a factory or source raw materials. Just take the email =
that is like =E2=80=9Csend me $1 million and I will get you a guaranteed 20=
% return in a month by yield farming in DeFi=E2=80=9D and search-and-replac=
e =E2=80=9Cyield farming in DeFi=E2=80=9D with =E2=80=9Cmanufacturing scarc=
e widgets.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/32142671.258409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaGhzLmdvdi9mb3JtdWxh=
L2luZGV4Lmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfa211ead" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">supplying scarce=
 baby formula</a>.=E2=80=9D Or =E2=80=9Cproviding medical aid to Ukraine.=
=E2=80=9D Or =E2=80=9Cimporting N95 masks to fight Covid.=E2=80=9D If you r=
ead the news and see that there=E2=80=99s a high-profile shortage of some g=
ood, you can just pretend to supply it! And gullible investors, who also re=
ad the news, will be excited to give you money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not any sort of advice, I do not recom=
mend it, I would not do it myself, but oh boy did Eliyahu Weinstein (allege=
dly) do it.=C2=A0In 2013, Weinstein pleaded guilty to running a $200 millio=
n real estate Ponzi scheme. In 2012 and 2013, while he was out on bail for =
that Ponzi scheme, he did another financial scam <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32142671.258409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9s=
aXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9jb21wLXByMjAyMy0xMzQucGRm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB7553e812" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> involving</a> =E2=80=9Cpurported sales of pr=
e-IPO Facebook shares and Florida real estate=E2=80=9D; he pleaded guilty t=
o that one in 2014. He was sentenced to a total of 24 years in prison for a=
ll of this, but in January 2021 President Donald Trump <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32142671.258409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW=
1lcy5jb20vMjAyMy8wNy8xOS9ueXJlZ2lvbi9wb256aS1zY2hlbWUtZnJhdWQtdHJ1bXAtY29tb=
XV0ZS1zZW50ZW5jZS5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB672d59d1" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">commuted=
 his sentence</a> and let him out of prison. I don=E2=80=99t know why Trump=
 let him out, but possibly he admired Weinstein=E2=80=99s moxie and sense o=
f humor and wanted to see what else he=E2=80=99d get up to.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That faith in him was richly rewarded yesterda=
y, when Weinstein was charged by the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32142671.258409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNz=
LXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0xMzQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa91e12c8" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> US Secu=
rities and Exchange Commission</a> and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/32142671.258409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby=
1uai9wci9jb252aWN0ZWQtcG9uemktc2NoZW1lci1mb3VyLW90aGVyLW1lbi1jaGFyZ2VkLW11b=
HRpbWlsbGlvbi1kb2xsYXItZnJhdWQtc2NoZW1lLWFuZA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB38cc=
d520" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;"> federal prosecutors in New Jersey</a> with doing a new Ponzi=
 scheme in the two years since he left prison. Pre-IPO Facebook shares were=
 very much the current thing in 2012, before Facebook went public, but in 2=
021 through 2023 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
2142671.258409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvZDkvMjAyMy0wNy93ZWluc3RlaW5l=
dGFsLmNvbXBsYWludC5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9f173ba1" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the thi=
ngs were apparently</a>:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CIn or around late 2021, Optim=
us [one of Weinstein=E2=80=99s companies]=C2=A0started raising money direct=
ly from a small number of investors to finance purported transactions relat=
ed to COVID-19 medical supplies.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">=E2=80=9CIn or around May 2022, WEINSTEIN (posing as Mike Konig) as=
ked CC-1 and CC-2 [<em>two unnamed alleged co-conspirators</em>] to raise m=
oney from investors to finance the purchase and delivery=C2=A0of three mill=
ion first-aid kits (=E2=80=98FAKs=E2=80=99) to USAID to be distributed to t=
he people of Ukraine during the Russia-Ukraine war (the =E2=80=98FAK deal=
=E2=80=99).=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CIn o=
r around May 2022, WEINSTEIN (posing as Mike Konig), asked CC-1 and CC-2 to=
 raise additional money to finance Company-1=E2=80=99s purchase of 100 mill=
ion N95 masks (the =E2=80=98N95 Mask deal=E2=80=99).=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CSimilarly, in or around early August 2=
022, WEINSTEIN (posing as Mike Konig) asked CC-1 and CC-2 to raise money to=
 finance the purchase of approximately 29 shipping containers of baby formu=
la from [<em>alleged co-conspirator Alaa Mohamed</em>] HATTAB=E2=80=99s com=
pany, Hattab Global, in order to capitalize on supply chain issues which ha=
d created a=C2=A0shortage in baby formula (the =E2=80=98Formula deal=E2=80=
=99).=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just pick a thing in the news, and he was alle=
gedly pretending to supply it. Of course prosecutors say he was not actuall=
y doing any of these things and was instead stealing the money, then raisin=
g more (from the next thing) to Ponzi it up and pay fake returns to the ear=
lier investors. If you raise money from investors to pretend to source Covi=
d-19 supplies, and you tell them it was a huge success, then you can raise =
more money from investors to pretend to supply medical aid to Ukraine and u=
se that money to pay your fake returns to the Covid people. Here=E2=80=99s =
a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32142671.258409/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9jb21wLXByMjA=
yMy0xMzQucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC7553e812" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">sample pitch email=
</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We successfully completed our firs=
t formula deal with 4 x 28,200 800g Cans (4 Containers). That=E2=80=99s 112=
,200 cans of formula being distributed to families in Texas at fair prices.=
 Needless to say, we felt so good about this one, that we have another deal=
 in the pipeline for 29 more containers. And it is LIVE. If you want in on =
this deal, Offering is 25% within 3-4 Months (Although we think it will be =
faster). Funding on this is open from 8/08-8/19. ACt [sic] now,=E2=80=A6 On=
ly 4mm in funding room left!</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It seems that Weinstein called himself =E2=80=
=9CMike Konig=E2=80=9D for the obvious reason that he had an extensive crim=
inal record for frauds and didn=E2=80=99t want potential investors to know =
about it. (=E2=80=9CNo one would ever give=C2=A0you a penny if they knew wh=
o I was . . . because I have a bad reputation,=E2=80=9D Weinstein allegedly=
 said at a meeting recorded by law enforcement, oops.) And=C2=A0some of his=
 alleged co-conspirators knew him as Mike Konig until this alleged hilariou=
s dramatic reveal:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or about August 26, 2022, WEINSTEIN, BROMBE=
RG, HATTAB, CC-1, and CC-2 met in a hotel conference room in or around Bran=
chburg, New Jersey. Law enforcement obtained a surreptitious audio recordin=
g of that meeting.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During the meeting, WEINSTEIN stated to CC-1 a=
nd CC-2, =E2=80=9CI can=E2=80=99t do this with =E2=80=98Mike [Konig]=E2=80=
=99 anymore. I am Eli Weinstein.=E2=80=9D As discussed above, WEINSTEIN als=
o admitted that (a) the [bills of lading] for the Formula deal were false, =
and (b) he diverted money from the N95 Mask deal for other purposes, includ=
ing to invest in the Turkish stock market.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also they had a later meeting, also recorded, =
to further emphasize what crimes they were doing:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or about August 29 and 31, 2022, WEINSTEIN,=
 WITTELS, BROMBERG, EREZ, and CC-2 met in a hotel conference room in or aro=
und Allentown, Pennsylvania. Law enforcement obtained surreptitious audio r=
ecordings of these meetings. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During the August 31 meeting, when discussing =
purported Optimus deals, WEINSTEIN admitted that he =E2=80=9Cmisrepresented=
 specific things=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cmisled=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Clied ab=
out transactions.=E2=80=9D WEINSTEIN also acknowledged that the FAK deal di=
d not happen but claimed HATTAB misappropriated the money for Saniton Plast=
ic. WEINSTEIN also admitted to engaging in the Ponzi Scheme, stating, =E2=
=80=9CI finagled, and Ponzied, and lied to people to cover us.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the way, if you were the guy at these meeti=
ngs who=C2=A0<em>didn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>know that Weinstein was a twice-c=
onvicted criminal and that all the deals were fake, and then he confessed e=
verything, what would you do? Three possible answers would be:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Change your name, grow a mustache and=
 run away to sea.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Go to the FBI im=
mediately, tell them everything, assure them that you had no idea and were =
totally innocent, offer to wear a wire to catch Weinstein, etc. This seems =
reasonable? (Not legal advice!) They=E2=80=99re going want to get Weinstein=
 again, so they=E2=80=99ll probably give you a decent deal even if you were=
 doing a little bit of crime before the big reveal.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">Just be like =E2=80=9Ceh, nobody=E2=80=99s perfect=E2=80=
=9D and continue doing the scam?=C2=A0</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It would not be my choice, but prosecutors say=
 that they went with Option 3:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Both during and after these August=
 2022 meetings, the Conspirators agreed to continue concealing WEINSTEIN=E2=
=80=99s identity from investors and to raise additional money to pay off ex=
isting Tryon investors, all in an effort to stop=C2=A0the Ponzi Scheme from=
 falling apart and to cover up the Defendants=E2=80=99 fraud.</p></blockquo=
